_reflns_special_details
;
 Structure factors included contributions from the .fab file.
 
 _reflns_Friedel_fraction is defined as the number of unique
 Friedel pairs measured divided by the number that would be
 possible theoretically, ignoring centric projections and
 systematic absences. Completness statistics refer to single and
 composite reflections containing twin component 1 only.
The 'soft' restraint with a large esd (ISOR) and similarity restraint on displacement 
amplitudes (SIMU) were employed globally to atomic displacement parameters of disordered 
C70 molecules, as well as the disordered diflurobenzene fragments. The 1,2-distances of atoms
in these molecules were restrainted to be similar by means of the similar restraint (SAME). 
The solvent contributions have been removed using the SQUEEZE procedure in PLATON
;
 
